included.description:
I worked as a Usability Researcher for the Universal Store Team at Microsoft. My role was divided between usability research as well as project management for the Store team. Highlights of my work and responsibilities included:

â¢ Developed metrics to quantify value and impact of the research that the Store team conducted
â¢ Ensured projects stay on track by conducting weekly one on one meetings with team members and created a research tracking organizational tool to manage team priorities
â¢ Designed and executed a three-part longitudinal research study to assess discoverability, usability and user retention for apps within the Windows Store
â¢ Shared research findings to key stakeholders including project managers, data scientists and developers and sent results summary to 100+ members of the Windows Research Organization
â¢ Managed and conducted cross-disciplinary research to help partner local and international teams from Store Marketing and Microsoft Office
included.title: UX Researcher
